  h4 class="pb-2 text-lg font-bold text-left underline"
    ' How We Protect the Information
  p class="pb-4"
    ' The security, integrity and confidentiality of your information are extremely important to us. We have implemented  appropriate physical, electronic, and administrative  procedures to safeguard and secure User information from unauthorized access, disclosure, use and modification. Our website uses a Transport Layer Security, the standard security technology for establishing an encrypted (i.e. secure or private) link between a web server and a browser. All online donation transactions are handled by only vendors who are compliant with the Payment Card Industry (PCI).
  p class="pb-4"
    ' PCI refers to the technical and operational standards that businesses must follow to ensure that credit card data provided by cardholders is protected. Please understand, however, that no security system is impenetrable. We cannot guarantee that the information that you supply will not be intercepted while being transmitted to and from us over the Internet. In particular, email sent to or from the Platform may not be secure, and you should, therefore, take special care in deciding what information you choose to send to us via unsecured email. 

