  h4 class="pb-2 text-lg font-bold text-left underline"
    ' Your privacy rights
  p class="pb-4"
    ' Consumers in a number of states in the United States have certain rights with respect to the collection and use of their Personal Information. Those rights vary by state or province. As required by the California Privacy Rights Act of 2020, we provide detailed information below regarding the data subject rights available to California residents. Residents in other states and provinces have similar rights and can find more detail by referencing the applicable privacy law.
