    li class="pb-2"
      span class="underline"
        ' Right to Correct Inaccurate Information.
      p class="pb-4"
        ' You may request that we correct inaccurate Personal Information that we maintain about you. Upon receipt of a verifiable request to correct inaccurate Personal Information, we will take into account the nature of the Personal Information and the purposes for which we process it. We may require documentation from you in order to process your request where we have reliable documentation showing the accuracy of the information.
    li class="pb-2"
      span class="underline"
        ' Right to Request Deletion of Your Personal Information.
      p class="pb-4"
        ' You may also have the right to request that we delete Personal Information collected or maintained by us. Following receipt of a verifiable request to delete, we will let you know what, if any, Personal Information we can delete from our records. We will also notify our service providers and contractors, and any third parties to which we transferred your information about your request to delete. If we cannot delete all of your Personal Information, we will provide an explanation.
    li class="pb-2"
      span class="underline"
        ' Right to Appeal Decision
      p class="pb-4"
        ' If you are a California, Colorado, Connecticut, or Virginia resident, and you would like to submit an appeal about our decision to your request regarding your Personal Information, you may contact us at info@givingconnection.org. We respond to all appeal requests as soon as we reasonably can and no later than legally required.
    li class="pb-2"
      span class="underline"
        ' Right to Non-Discrimination for the Exercise of Your Privacy Rights
      p class="pb-4"
        ' If you choose to exercise any of the privacy rights described above, we will not discriminate against you. This means that, consistent with applicable state privacy law, we will not deny providing our products or services to you, charge you different prices, or provide a different level or quality of products or services to you unless those differences are related to the value of your Personal Information.
